o verify accuracy. The first section looks correct with the image path and parent class notes preserved, and the table data matches. For the second section, I'm comparing how the MockMessagingContext functionality is described—the source emphasizes the assertion capability after Action execution, and the knowledge file captures this same core idea.\n\nContinuing through sections three and four, both check out. The numbered list in section five aligns with the source bullet points. But in section six, I'm noticing a potential issue: the source includes \"必要に応じて\" (as needed/when necessary) before mentioning XML and JSON implementation, but the knowledge file omits this qualifier. This distinction matters because it indicates the implementation isn't always required, just when circumstances call for it.\n\nLooking more closely at the class description at the top of the file, it does include this qualifier, so the knowledge file is inconsistent with itself. It's a subtle omission rather than outright fabrication, but it does shift the meaning from optional to mandatory. Now I need to examine section seven more carefully.\n\nThe source uses \"基本的な記述方法\" (basic writing method) while the knowledge file just says \"記述方法\" (writing method) - dropping the \"basic\" qualifier. It's a minor difference that doesn't fundamentally change the meaning.\n\nLooking at the RST structure, I see the headings are organized as h2 for 概要 and h3 for 全体像, which suggests they're meant to be nested sections rather than separate top-level sections.\n\nThe document structure shows multiple h2 sections under 概要 - 主なクラス, リソース, 構造, and テストデータ - with various h3 subsections underneath. The heading levels follow standard RST conventions where `====` marks h2 and `------` marks h3, so the hierarchy appears to be properly nested with the main title at h1 level. ドキュメント構造を確認しているところだ。セクション見出しは4つのh2レベル（概要、主なクラス、構造、テストデータ）と、その下に7つのh3セクションが配置されている。ナレッジファイルの7セクションはこれらのh3見出しに対応しているようで、全体像と主なクラスがs1に統合されているのに対し、各